{{Infobox person | honorific-prefix = [[His Excellency]] | name = Mohi-Din Binhendi | image = | image_size = 200 | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Director General of '''Dubai Civil Aviation Authority''' & [[President]] of [http://www.binhendi.com Binhendi Enterprises] | networth = Unknown Billionaires of Dollars in [[UAE]] }}
'''Mohi-Din Binhendi''' ([[Arabic]]:محيي الدين بن هندي), was appointed as the '''Director General''' of the [[Department of Civil Aviation]] of [[Dubai]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.flightglobal.com/articles/2007/11/11/219287/dubai-2007-a-show-of-strength.html|title=Dubai 2007: A show of strength|date=November 11, 2007|work=Flight Daily News|accessdate=25 June 2011}}</ref> and as the [[CEO]] of [[Dubai International Airport]] in June 1979 by special decree issued by the [[Ruler (potentate)|ruler]] of Dubai Sheikh [[Rashid bin Saeed Al Maktoum]], having previously served as Director of airport customs.
He was a member of the Board of Governors at Dubai Aviation College, a member of the Board of Directors at Emirates Golf Club, and Chairman of the Aviation Advisory Committee at Dubai Men's College.
Binhendi was awarded the [[Decoration of Honour for Services to the Republic of Austria|''Grand Decoration of Honour in Silver'' for Services to the Republic of Austria]] by the [[President of Austria]] in January 1995.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.parlament.gv.at/PAKT/VHG/XXIV/AB/AB_10542/imfname_251156.pdf | title = Reply to a parliamentary question about the Decoration of Honour | language = German | page=975 |trans-title=| format = pdf | accessdate = November 2012 }}</ref> In January 1996 Binhendi was awarded the 'Honour of the Order of Merit of the Republic' with the title 'Cavalière' by the [[President]] of the [[Republic of Italy]] for the promotion and strengthening of cultural and commercial links between [[Italy]] and the UAE {{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}. With his guidance, BinHendi became one of the first UAE-based groups to franchise its own locally-born brands.<ref>{{cite web|title=Website|url=http://www.binhendi.com/directors/mohi-din-binhendi/|accessdate=3 February 2017}}</ref>
==Family business== Binhendi Enterprises LLC.
==Education== After completing his High School Diploma in [[Dubai]], he earned his Business Administration Graduate in the [[United States of America]].
